channel.title: Documentation Not Included
channel.description: Documentation Not Included is a live-streamed development talk show and podcast where Josey and Chris delve deep into all things development. We're platform agnostic, covering topics such as web development, process work-flows, enterprise architecture, game development, visual effects, community management, virtual assistance and DevOps practices. We also cover a vast array of other topics related to IT in general. We stream live every Thursday at 7PM GMT (https://twitch.tv/dnistream) on Twitch. Come join us and have your say!
channel.itunes:subtitle: The podcast for developers by developers with other IT added for fun!

item.itunes:summary:
Andy Morrell joins Chris and Josey this week to discuss how to stay relevant as a developer. Is the answer learning by osmosis? Ancient blood rituals? Listen to find out!

TOPICS

  • Whether permie or freelance, stagnation happens. How to avoid it.
  • Learning lessons
  • Taking on new technologies and frameworks
  • How your type of job, and work culture, can impact your ability to stay relevant
  • ...and so much more!

item.content:encoded:
In a special 2 hour episode, Chris and Josey are joined by Jamie from the donetcoreshow to discuss one of the biggest topics we've tried to avoid this year; IR35. What is it? Does it impact freelancers? Contractors? What happens when the gloves come off and the team has their say?

TOPICS

  • What is IR35?
  • Who is impacted by it?
  • How do you know if you are caught, or not?
  • What impact is this having right now on contractors and freelancers in the IT world?
  • ...and a whole lot more. After all this is a special 2 hour episode!
